### [01. Common Core]
*The main engineering track. These projects focus on building robust, reusable libraries and understanding system-level I/O.*

#### [Circle 0 & 1: The Foundations]
| Project | Description & Key Concepts | Status |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Libft** | **The Standard Library:** Reimplementing 40+ standard functions (e.g., `memset`, `calloc`). | ‚úÖ Done |
| **ft_printf** | **Variadic Functions:** Managing variable argument lists to mimic `printf`. | ‚úÖ Done |
| **get_next_line**| **Static Variables:** Reading lines from file descriptors without memory leaks. | ‚úÖ Done |
| **Born2beroot** | **Virtualization:** Setting up a strict Debian server with LVM, SSH, and UFW. | ‚úÖ Done |

#### [Circle 2: Complexity & Communication]
| Project | Description & Key Concepts | Status |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **fract-ol** | **2D Graphics:** Real-time Mandelbrot/Julia sets using complex math and MiniLibX. | ‚úÖ Done |
| **minitalk** | **IPC & Bitwise Logic:** Data exchange using UNIX signals (`SIGUSR1`/`SIGUSR2`). | ‚úÖ Done |

### [Exam Rank 02 Preparation]
*Location: `/42 Exam Rank 02`* Algorithmic challenges solved under time pressure without external libraries.
* **Level 1 & 2:** String searches, bitwise operations, and `atoi` implementation.
* **Level 3 & 4:** Advanced math (`lcm`) and linked list manipulation.

